    <fr:title text="Internal characterisation of being Heyting">Internal characterisation of being Heyting</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Proposition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  A scheme <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/schm-FZCT/" title="Heyting and Boolean schemes" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-FZCT/" display-uri="schm-FZCT" type="local">Heyting/Boolean</fr:link> iff <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_{X}]]></fr:tex> is internally a Heyting/Boolean algebra.
</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>11</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <html:p>
    If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_{X}]]></fr:tex> is a Heyting algebra, then we have an explicit morphism
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ (-) \to  (-) : \mathcal {O}_{X}^{\mathrm {op}} \times  \mathcal {O}_{X} \to  \mathcal {O}_{X} ]]></fr:tex>
    over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>. This induces an implication operator on each affine open <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} A]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, which must be the implication operator, since when we have a function symbol, being the implication operator is an equational property. This implies <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> must be Heyting.
  </html:p>
  <html:p>
    On the other hand, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is Heyting, then for any affine open <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} A]]></fr:tex> there is a Heyting implication
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ (-) \to _A (-) : \mathcal {O}_{X}(\operatorname {Spec} A)^{\mathrm {op}} \times  \mathcal {O}_{X}(\operatorname {Spec} A) \cong  A^{\mathrm {op}} \times  A \to  A \cong  \mathcal {O}_{X}(\operatorname {Spec} A) ]]></fr:tex>
    Furthermore, they must agree on intersections because the implication is uniquely determined. This way all the local implications glue together to provide an implication for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_{X}]]></fr:tex>, and it will be the internal Heyting implication by the Kripke-Joyal semantics.
  </html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
